                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1906</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 98.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith a
                    chronological record of the different administrations of government of the
                    Republic of Uruguay from November, 1828, when the general constitutional and
                    legislative assembly was installed, to March 1, 1906.</p>
                <p>This record shows, among other things, that during the seventy-seven years since
                    the adoption of its constitution the Government of Uruguay has had 15
                    Presidents, 4 Vice-Presidents who became Presidents, 15 presidents of the Senate
                    who exercised the duties of President without relinquishing the duties of the
                    presidency of the Senate, 5 dictators, a triumvirate of dictators, and 4
                    provisional governors, with 1 triumvirate of governors.</p>
                <p>This is the first of a series of papers being carefully arranged by me from the
                    government records, intended to give a complete chronological history of the
                    political and financial affairs of the Republic since the adoption of the
                    constitution.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward C. O’Brien.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
